						               													<description>Little Lead Wars is a simple, old-fashioned game to play with traditional toy soldiers &amp;ndash; it could be considered a &amp;ldquo;toygame&amp;rdquo; as much as a wargame in its slightly abstract approach to warfare. &amp;#10;A match-less successor to the spirit of HG Wells' Little Wars and Dowdall &amp;amp; Gleason's Sham Battle, &amp;#10;Little Lead Wars takes up only two sides of A4 paper in bringing you fun for all the family.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Included are all the usual rules for differentiating infantry, cavalry, artillery and their use on the battlefield, as well as a page of extra optional rules for slightly more complex play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Morningstar's Tactical Two Pager games are a series of simple but engaging games with fun and flavour. Each one takes up only two sides of A4, eliminating the need for a quick reference sheet and providing a cheap source of entertainment to our players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
